                  <foliation/>
                  <collation>
                    <p>The quires, 20 in number, were originally signed with arithmetical figures (e.g. <locus from="167" to="167">fol. 167</locus>, <!-- NEED ARABIC -->; <locus from="177" to="177">fol. 177</locus>, <!-- NEED ARABIC -->; and <locus from="187" to="187">fol. 187</locus>, <foreign xml:lang="ar"><!-- NEED ARABIC --></foreign>); but another hand has marked them with letters on the last leaf of each quire.</p>
                  </collation>
                  <condition>
                    <list>
                      <item>
                        <p>Some leaves are much stained and torn, especially foll. <locus from="4" to="4">4</locus>, <locus from="12" to="21">12—21</locus>, and <locus from="193" to="196">193—196</locus>.</p>
                      </item>
                      <item>
                        <p>Leaves are now wanting after foll. <locus from="49" to="49">49</locus> and <locus from="77" to="77">77</locus>.</p>
                      </item>
                      <item>
                        <p><ref target="#additon5">See additions.</ref></p>
                      </item>
                    </list>
                  </condition>
                </supportDesc>
                <layoutDesc>
                  <layout columns="2" writtenLines="23 26">
                    <p>Each page is divided into two columns, of from 23 to 26 lines.</p>
                  </layout>
                </layoutDesc>
              </objectDesc>
              <handDesc hands="9">
                <handNote xml:id="handNote1" scope="major" script="syr-Syre" medium="unknown">
                  <desc>The writing is a fine bold Estrangela, of the <origDate notBefore="0500" notAfter="0600">6th century</origDate>.</desc>
                </handNote>
                <handNote xml:id="handNote2" scope="minor" script="syr" medium="unknown">
                  <desc>An inelegant, angular hand of about the <date notBefore="1000" notAfter="1100">11th century</date>. <ref target="#addition5 #addition6">See additions.</ref></desc>
                </handNote>
                <handNote xml:id="handNote3" scope="minor" script="syr" medium="unknown">
                  <desc>A hand of <date notBefore="1100" notAfter="1870">still later date</date>. <ref target="#addition7">See additions.</ref></desc>
                </handNote>
                <handNote xml:id="handNote4" scope="minor" script="syr" medium="unknown">
                  <desc><ref target="#addition1">See additions.</ref></desc>
                </handNote>
                <handNote xml:id="handNote5" scope="minor" script="syr" medium="unknown">
                  <desc><ref target="#addition2">See additions.</ref></desc>
                </handNote>
                <handNote xml:id="handNote6" scope="minor" script="ar" medium="unknown">
                  <desc><ref target="#addition3">See additions.</ref></desc>
                </handNote>
                <handNote xml:id="handNote7" scope="minor" script="ar" medium="unknown">
                  <desc>A modern hand. <ref target="#addition4">See additions.</ref></desc>
                </handNote>
                <handNote xml:id="handNote8" scope="minor" script="ar-Syrc" medium="unknown">
                  <desc>Written in Karshuni. <ref target="#addition8">See additions.</ref></desc>
                </handNote>
                <handNote xml:id="handNote9" scope="minor" script="ar" medium="unknown">
                  <desc><ref target="#addition9">See additions.</ref></desc>
                </handNote>
              </handDesc>
              <decoDesc/>
              <additions>
                <list>
                  <item n="1" xml:id="addition1">
                    <ref target="#handNote4"/>
                    <p>Another hand has marked the quires with letters on the last leaf of each quire.</p>
                  </item>
                  <item n="2" xml:id="addition2">
                    <ref target="#handNote5"/>
                    <p>At a still later period, the volume has been wrongly divided into 22 quires, signed with letters at the beginning and end of each.</p>
                  </item>
                  <item n="3" xml:id="addition3">
                    <ref target="#handNote6"/>
                    <p>A great many lessons have been noted by several later hands, one of them in Arabic (<locus from="121b" to="121b">fol. 121 b</locus>).</p>
                  </item>
                  <item n="4" xml:id="addition4">
                    <ref target="#handNote7"/>
                    <p>A modern hand has divided the text into sections, designated by <foreign xml:lang="syr">ܦܨ</foreign> (<!-- NEED ARABIC -->). Of these there are 84 in <ref target="#b1">S. Matthew</ref>, 49 in <ref target="#b2">S. Mark</ref>, 88 in <ref target="#b3">S. Luke</ref>, and 45 in <ref target="#b4">S. John</ref>.</p>
                  </item>
                  <item n="5" xml:id="addition5">
                    <ref target="#handNote2"/>
                    <p>Foll. <locus from="2" to="3">2, 3</locus>, and <locus from="5" to="5">5</locus> are written in an inelegant, angular hand of about the <date notBefore="1000" notAfter="1100">11th century</date>. The same person has repaired foll. <locus from="13" to="17">13-17</locus>, in one case (<locus from="16" to="16">fol. 16</locus>) with a piece of an Arabic manuscript. Other portions have been retouched at different times.</p>
                  </item>
                  <item n="6" xml:id="addition6">
                    <locus from="3b" to="3b"/>
                    <ref target="#handNote2"/>
                    <p>On fol. 3 b the later scribe has written more than was necessary to connect it with <locus from="4" to="4">fol. 4</locus>, so that ch. ii. 4—6, from <quote xml:lang="syr">ܗܘܐ ܠܗܘܢ ܕܐܝܟܐ ܡܬܝܠܕ ܒܨܝܪܐ</quote> to <quote xml:lang="syr">ܠܐ ܗܘܬ</quote> is repeated.</p>
                  </item>
                  <item n="7" xml:id="addition7">
                    <locus from="133" to="133"/>
                    <ref target="#handNote3"/>
                    <p>Fol. 133 is a <material>paper</material> leaf of still later date, with writing on one side only.</p>
                  </item>
                  <item n="8" xml:id="addition8">
                    <locus from="15a" to="15a"/>
                    <ref target="#handNote8"/>
                    <p>On fol. 15 a, at the foot of the page, is written in Karshūnī,</p>
                    <p><quote xml:lang="ar-Syrc">ܝܐ ܪܒ ܬܪܚܡ ܥܠܝ ܥܒܝܕܟ ܐܘܠܕܝ ܠܟܢܝܣܗ ܠܡܩܕܣܗ</quote>,</p>
                    <p>i.e.,</p>
                    <p><quote xml:lang="ar"><!-- NEED ARABIC --></quote></p>
                  </item>
                  <item n="9" xml:id="addition9">
                    <ref target="#handNote9"/>
                    <p>Foll. <locus from="1b" to="2a">1b, 2 a</locus>, and <locus from="133b" to="133b">133 b</locus>, are covered with what seem to be mere exercises in writing, in the Arabic character.</p>
                  </item>
                </list>
              </additions>
